# Bitstream Telemetry Provider (external apps)

When the user or task builds **external telemetry consumers** (Course HTML blocks, React localhost dashboards, third-party live UI):

## Portable developer kit (canonical)

**Upload folder:** `extension/docs/bitstream-telemetry-provider/`

| File | Role |
|------|------|
| `SKILL.md` | AI agent checklist (start here) |
| `RECIPES.md` | Progress bars, gauge mapping, aliases |
| `EXAMPLES/gyro-x-progress-bar.html` | Single-file HTML reference |
| `README.md` | Human overview |
| `EVENTS.md`, `IFRAME.md`, `SDK.md`, `ADVANCED.md` | Consumer docs |
| `sensor-catalog.v1.json`, `SCHEMA.v1.json` | Machine-readable specs |

Cursor discovery skill: `.cursor/skills/bitstream-telemetry-provider/SKILL.md` → points to kit `SKILL.md`.

## Contract

- Public events: `bitstream:*` envelope `{ type, v: 1, payload }`
- Live values: **`bitstream:sample`** → `payload.fields` (human-scale)
- Specs: **`bitstream:catalog`** + **`sensor-catalog.v1.json`**
- Config: **`bitstream:config`** (push on change only)
- **Do not** parse BS2 UART in app code

## Transports

| Consumer | Use |
|----------|-----|
| Course iframe | `postMessage` — `IFRAME.md` in kit |
| localhost React | SDK → **`ws://127.0.0.1:9997`** — `SDK.md` in kit |
| Expert / Node | R2 raw broker 9998 — `ADVANCED.md` in kit |

## Catalog changes (repo contributors)

Edit `src/bitstream2/telemetry-provider/catalog/sensor-catalog-source.ts`, then:

```bash
npm run bitstream2:telemetry-catalog:gen
npm run test:bitstream2
```

Regenerates JSON in the kit folder and `src/bitstream2/telemetry-provider/`.

## Communication

**Always DO NOT respond in Chinese.** Use **English** and/or **Thai** only — **`communication-language.mdc`**.

Keep **`extension/.cursor/rules/bitstream-telemetry-provider.mdc`** in sync when editing this file.
